---
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../../consts';
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
	<BaseHead 
		title={`Secure Document Shredders NZ | NSA-Approved Refurbished | Auckland`}
		description="Buy refurbished high-security document shredders in New Zealand. NSA/CSS approved, cross-cut and micro-cut models. Professional quality, Auckland-based."
		keywords="document shredder NZ, secure shredder Auckland, NSA approved shredder New Zealand, cross-cut shredder NZ, paper shredder Auckland, refurbished shredder"
	/>
</head>
<body>
	<a href="#main-content" class="skip-to-main">Skip to main content</a>
	<Header />
	<main id="main-content">
		<section class="hero">
			<div class="container">
				<h1>Refurbished Shredders</h1>
				<p class="tagline">High-Security Document Destruction</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="card">
					<div class="product-header">
						<span class="badge">NSA-Approved Security Levels</span>
					</div>
					<p class="product-intro">Professionally refurbished high-security paper shredders meeting NSA/CSS EPL and DIN security standards for classified document destruction. Each unit is thoroughly inspected, serviced, and tested to ensure reliable operation. Available in cross-cut (P-4/P-5) and micro-cut (P-6/P-7) security levels suitable for government, military, and enterprise document destruction requirements.</p>
					
					<h2>Technical Specifications</h2>
					
					<div class="specs-grid">
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Security Level Compliance</strong>
							<p>Units available in DIN P-4 through P-7 security levels. P-5 and above meet NSA/CSS 02-01 specifications for classified document destruction. Cross-cut models produce particles ≤ 4.0mm x 40mm. Micro-cut models produce particles ≤ 2.0mm x 15mm (P-6) or confetti-style micro-particles (P-7).</p>
						</div>
						
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Refurbishment Process</strong>
							<p>Complete teardown and inspection of mechanical components. Replacement of worn cutting blades, drive belts, and motor bearings. Electrical system testing and safety certification. Lubrication and calibration to manufacturer specifications. 90-day warranty on all refurbished units.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Cutting Mechanism</strong>
							<p>Hardened steel cutting cylinders with precision-ground edges. Cross-cut or micro-cut patterns depending on model. Designed for continuous operation with thermal overload protection. Capable of processing paper, staples, paper clips, and credit cards (model dependent).</p>
						</div>
						
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Capacity & Throughput</strong>
							<p>Sheet capacity ranges from 10-30 sheets per pass depending on model and security level. Bin sizes from 20L to 100L+. Heavy-duty models support continuous operation for high-volume environments. Automatic reverse for jam clearing.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Destruction Capabilities</strong>
							<p>Standard paper (20-80 gsm), cardstock, envelopes, photographs, staples, paper clips, credit cards, CDs/DVDs (model dependent). Some models include separate cutting mechanisms for optical media destruction. Maximum insertion width varies by model (220mm to 310mm).</p>
						</div>
						
						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Safety Features</strong>
							<p>Automatic shut-off when bin is full or removed. Safety interlock prevents operation with access panels open. Thermal protection against motor overheating. Child safety lock on power switch. Jam-proof technology with automatic reverse.</p>
						</div>

						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Operational Standards</strong>
							<p>Meets NSA/CSS EPL requirements for classified information disposal (P-5 and above). Compliant with HIPAA, FACTA, GLB Act for personal information destruction. Certified for EU GDPR data destruction requirements. Suitable for DoD contract environments.</p>
						</div>

						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Available Models</strong>
							<p>Commercial office models (15-20 sheet capacity), departmental models (20-25 sheet capacity), and industrial models (25-30 sheet capacity). Strip-cut, cross-cut, and micro-cut variants. Floor-standing and desktop configurations available based on inventory.</p>
						</div>

						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Duty Cycle</strong>
							<p>Continuous-duty motor with thermal protection in industrial models. Office models rated for 5-15 minutes continuous operation. Automatic cooldown period prevents motor damage. Heavy-duty models suitable for central shredding facilities.</p>
						</div>

						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Noise & Power</strong>
							<p>Noise levels range from 55-70 dB depending on model and security level. Power consumption 300W-2000W. Standard 230V power supply. Energy-efficient standby mode with automatic activation on document insertion.</p>
						</div>

						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Maintenance Support</strong>
							<p>Replacement blade sets available for extended service life. Oil sheets provided for regular lubrication. Detailed operational manual and maintenance schedule included. Technical support for operational issues and troubleshooting.</p>
						</div>

						<div class="spec-item">
							<strong>Quality Assurance</strong>
							<p>Each unit tested with 100+ sheet destruction cycles before delivery. Blade sharpness verification to ensure consistent particle size. Electrical safety testing and certification. Physical inspection of all mechanical components.</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<h2>Use Cases</h2>
					<div class="use-cases">
						<div class="use-case-item">
							<h4>Government & Defense</h4>
							<p>Classified document destruction meeting NSA/CSS EPL standards. Secure disposal of sensitive intelligence materials, operational plans, and personnel files.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="use-case-item">
							<h4>Healthcare & Legal</h4>
							<p>HIPAA-compliant destruction of patient records, medical documents, and confidential legal materials. Secure disposal of personally identifiable information (PII).</p>
						</div>
						<div class="use-case-item">
							<h4>Financial Services</h4>
							<p>Destruction of bank statements, loan documents, credit applications, and financial records meeting FACTA and GLB Act requirements for data protection.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="use-case-item">
							<h4>Corporate & SME</h4>
							<p>Secure disposal of proprietary information, business plans, employee records, and confidential communications. GDPR-compliant data destruction for EU operations.</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="notice">
						<h3>About Refurbished Units</h3>
						<p><strong>Quality Guarantee:</strong> All refurbished shredders undergo comprehensive testing and servicing to ensure reliable operation. While cosmetic wear may be present, all mechanical and safety systems meet manufacturer specifications.</p>
						<p><strong>Inventory Varies:</strong> Available models and security levels depend on current inventory. Contact us for specific model availability, specifications, and pricing. We source units from office liquidations, government surplus, and corporate upgrades.</p>
						<p><strong>Environmental Benefit:</strong> Refurbished equipment provides high-security document destruction at reduced cost while extending product lifecycle and reducing electronic waste.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="back-to-products">
					<a href="/products" class="btn secondary">← Back to Products</a>
					<a href="mailto:hello@hermetrix.nz" class="btn primary">Inquire About Availability</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
	<Footer />

	<style>
		.hero {
			padding: var(--space-3xl) 0 var(--space-2xl);
		}

		.tagline {
			font-size: 1.25rem;
			color: var(--text-secondary);
			margin-top: var(--space-md);
			font-family: var(--font-family-mono);
			text-transform: uppercase;
			letter-spacing: 0.15em;
		}

		.card {
			background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);
			backdrop-filter: blur(5px);
		}

		.product-header {
			margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
		}

		.badge {
			display: inline-block;
			padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
			background: rgba(0, 204, 82, 0.1);
			border: 2px solid var(--acid-green);
			border-radius: 6px;
			font-size: 0.75rem;
			font-weight: 700;
			color: var(--acid-green);
			font-family: var(--font-family-mono);
			text-transform: uppercase;
			letter-spacing: 0.1em;
			box-shadow: 3px 3px 0 rgba(0, 204, 82, 0.2);
		}

		.product-intro {
			font-size: 1.125rem;
			margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
			color: var(--text-secondary);
			line-height: 1.8;
		}

		.card h2 {
			color: var(--acid-green);
			font-size: 1.875rem;
			margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
			margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
			text-transform: uppercase;
			letter-spacing: 0.05em;
		}

		.specs-grid {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
			gap: var(--space-lg);
			margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
		}

		.spec-item {
			padding: var(--space-lg);
			background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
			backdrop-filter: blur(3px);
			border: 2px solid var(--white);
			border-radius: 6px;
			box-shadow: 4px 4px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
			transition: all 0.3s ease;
		}

		.spec-item:hover {
			border-color: var(--acid-green);
			transform: translate(-2px, -2px);
			box-shadow: 6px 6px 0 rgba(0, 204, 82, 0.3);
		}

		.spec-item strong {
			display: block;
			color: var(--acid-green);
			margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
			font-size: 1rem;
			font-weight: 700;
			text-transform: uppercase;
			letter-spacing: 0.05em;
		}

		.spec-item p {
			margin: 0;
			font-size: 0.9375rem;
			line-height: 1.6;
			color: var(--text-secondary);
		}

		.use-cases {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
			gap: var(--space-lg);
			margin-top: var(--space-xl);
		}

		.use-case-item {
			padding: var(--space-lg);
			background: rgba(0, 204, 82, 0.05);
			border: 2px solid var(--acid-green);
			border-radius: 6px;
			transition: all 0.3s ease;
		}

		.use-case-item:hover {
			background: rgba(0, 204, 82, 0.1);
			transform: translateY(-2px);
		}

		.use-case-item h4 {
			color: var(--acid-green);
			margin: 0 0 var(--space-sm) 0;
			font-size: 1.125rem;
			text-transform: uppercase;
			letter-spacing: 0.05em;
		}

		.use-case-item p {
			margin: 0;
			font-size: 0.9375rem;
			color: var(--text-secondary);
			line-height: 1.6;
		}

		.notice {
			padding: var(--space-xl);
			background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
			backdrop-filter: blur(5px);
			border-left: 4px solid var(--acid-green);
			border-radius: 6px;
			box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 204, 82, 0.1);
			margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
		}

		.notice h3 {
			color: var(--acid-green);
			margin-top: 0;
			margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
			font-weight: 900;
			font-size: 1.5rem;
		}

		.notice p {
			margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
			color: var(--text-secondary);
			line-height: 1.7;
		}

		.notice p:last-child {
			margin-bottom: 0;
		}

		.notice strong {
			color: var(--acid-green);
			font-weight: 700;
		}

		.back-to-products {
			margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
			display: flex;
			gap: var(--space-lg);
			justify-content: center;
			flex-wrap: wrap;
		}

		@media (max-width: 768px) {
			.hero {
				padding: var(--space-2xl) 0 var(--space-xl);
			}

			.specs-grid {
				grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			}

			.use-cases {
				grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			}

			.back-to-products {
				flex-direction: column;
			}

			.notice {
				padding: var(--space-lg);
			}
		}
	</style>
</body>
</html>
